feat(web): FastAPI app + single-page UI

Adds a built-in web UI + JSON API. Run with:
  yuroo-shield serve --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

Components:

- src/yuroo_shield/web.py: FastAPI app with two endpoints.
  - GET /api/health: returns config status + supported chains.
  - POST /api/scan: wraps AgentOrchestrator, accepts {address, chain},
    returns full ContractReport JSON. Validates 0x-prefixed 40-hex
    addresses and known chain IDs.
  - CORS open for browser fetches; static assets mounted under /assets.

- web/static/index.html: single-page UI, mobile-first.
  - Tailwind via CDN, JetBrains Mono for addresses.
  - Dark theme matching banner (#0a0e17 surface, accent #ff6b35,
    accent2 #00d4aa).
  - Live verdict card with risk-level color coding (safe/low green,
    medium yellow, high orange, critical red), score, canonical-token
    badge, MiMo summary panel, severity-sorted findings list.
  - Quick-pick examples: DAI, USDT, USDC, SHIB.
  - Loading state with rotating status messages.
  - Error state for invalid addresses or backend failures.
  - OG tags + favicon point to assets/banner.png.

- src/yuroo_shield/cli.py: adds `serve` subcommand that spawns uvicorn.

- pyproject.toml: adds fastapi>=0.110 and uvicorn[standard]>=0.27 to
  base dependencies.

- README: new Web UI section explaining the serve command, the UI,
  and the API endpoints.

Live-verified locally: GET /api/health returns ok with mimo-v2.5-pro
configured, POST /api/scan on DAI returns LOW(5) canonical:DAI as
expected. 28/28 tests still green.
